  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Imports & Data Loading"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QHtwRvPnXMkN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "uOsvt2MeXQs_"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Load data\n",
        "data = pd.read_csv(\"/content/double_helix_data_1000.csv\")\n",
        "X = data[['x', 'y', 'z']].values  # shape (N, 3)\n",
        "N, D = X.shape"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5WGMPFNYXUA9"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Model Hyperparameters"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "i3QSLr9sXVQS"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "K = 48                # number of components\n",
        "R = 12.0              # radius in feet\n",
        "H = 80.0              # height in feet\n",
        "two_pi = 2.0 * np.pi"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kehHJ1ahXYmS"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Initialize means on two helices"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cnSBgqJcXZvE"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 24 angles per staircase: j = 0..23, t_j = j * pi/6\n",
        "t_vals = np.array([j * np.pi / 6.0 for j in range(24)])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7gHlMYGMXfWC"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Staircase 1\n",
        "x1 = R * np.cos(t_vals)\n",
        "y1 = R * np.sin(t_vals)\n",
        "z1 = (H / (4.0 * np.pi)) * t_vals\n",
        "mu1 = np.stack([x1, y1, z1], axis=1)  # shape (24, 3)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ipzIKhwpXgnC"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Staircase 2: rotated by pi around z-axis\n",
        "x2 = -R * np.cos(t_vals)\n",
        "y2 = -R * np.sin(t_vals)\n",
        "z2 = (H / (4.0 * np.pi)) * t_vals\n",
        "mu2 = np.stack([x2, y2, z2], axis=1)  # shape (24, 3)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KcjHzyAqXhwo"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Full mean matrix mu: k=0..47\n",
        "mu = np.vstack([mu1, mu2])  # shape (48, 3)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "k96N9cJfXi_T"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Initialize Mixing Weights"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "satnkQpeXlmR"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "pi_k = np.ones(K) / K  # uniform weights 1/48"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tHFj8N4rXou8"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Initialize Covariances aligned with Staircase Tangents"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4nxtK1boXpgN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def make_covariances(mu, R=R, H=H):\n",
        "    # Build initial covariances Sigma_k = U diag(sig_par^2, sig_perp^2, sig_z^2) U^T aligned with helix tangents.\n",
        "    Sigmas = np.zeros((K, D, D))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Chosen scales\n",
        "    sig_par = 3.0   # along-stair direction\n",
        "    sig_perp = 1.0  # across-stairs\n",
        "    sig_z = 1.0     # vertical small variation\n",
        "\n",
        "    for k in range(K):\n",
        "        # Infer t from z coordinate (reverse of z(t) = (H / (4pi)) t)\n",
        "        z = mu[k, 2]\n",
        "        t = (4.0 * np.pi / H) * z   # approximate t\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Tangent vector\n",
        "        vx = -R * np.sin(t)\n",
        "        vy =  R * np.cos(t)\n",
        "        vz =  H / (4.0 * np.pi)\n",
        "        v = np.array([vx, vy, vz], dtype=float)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Normalize -> u1\n",
        "        u1 = v / np.linalg.norm(v)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Radial direction in xy-plane\n",
        "        vr = np.array([np.cos(t), np.sin(t), 0.0], dtype=float)\n",
        "        # Make orthogonal to u1\n",
        "        vr = vr - np.dot(vr, u1) * u1\n",
        "        u2 = vr / np.linalg.norm(vr)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Third axis: u3 = u1 x u2\n",
        "        u3 = np.cross(u1, u2)\n",
        "        u3 = u3 / np.linalg.norm(u3)\n",
        "\n",
        "        U = np.stack([u1, u2, u3], axis=1)  # 3x3\n",
        "\n",
        "        Lambda = np.diag([sig_par**2, sig_perp**2, sig_z**2])\n",
        "        Sigmas[k] = U @ Lambda @ U.T\n",
        "\n",
        "    return Sigmas"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UZSV_rixXw6k"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "Sigma = make_covariances(mu)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mxCa_f-lY7r9"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Multivariate Gaussian Density"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "w5mmF4kZXya-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def gaussian_pdf(x, mean, cov):\n",
        "    # Multivariate normal density N(x | mean, cov) for a single x (D,) or array (N,D).\n",
        "    x = np.atleast_2d(x)  # shape (N,D)\n",
        "    D = mean.shape[0]\n",
        "    det = np.linalg.det(cov)\n",
        "    inv = np.linalg.inv(cov)\n",
        "    norm_const = np.sqrt((2.0 * np.pi)**D * det)\n",
        "\n",
        "    diff = x - mean\n",
        "    expo = np.einsum('ni,ij,nj->n', diff, inv, diff)\n",
        "    return np.exp(-0.5 * expo) / norm_const"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "faRkNCiLX10y"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Constraint: Project Mean back onto nearest Helix"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xj71PwvDX3AT"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def project_to_helix(m, which_helix, R=R, H=H, n_grid=200):\n",
        "    # Project mean m=(x,y,z) onto the nearest point on helix 1 or 2. Which_helix: 1 or 2.\n",
        "    x, y, z = m\n",
        "    t_grid = np.linspace(0.0, 4.0 * np.pi, n_grid)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if which_helix == 1:\n",
        "        hx = R * np.cos(t_grid)\n",
        "        hy = R * np.sin(t_grid)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        hx = -R * np.cos(t_grid)\n",
        "        hy = -R * np.sin(t_grid)\n",
        "    hz = (H / (4.0 * np.pi)) * t_grid\n",
        "\n",
        "    pts = np.stack([hx, hy, hz], axis=1)  # (n_grid, 3)\n",
        "    diff = pts - m\n",
        "    d2 = np.sum(diff**2, axis=1)\n",
        "    j = np.argmin(d2)\n",
        "    return pts[j]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yDEgIS7KX9C2"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## EM Algorithm with Constraints"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nyHZBXVPX-rw"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def run_em(X, mu, Sigma, pi_k, max_iter=50, tol=1e-4):\n",
        "  N, D = X.shape\n",
        "  K = mu.shape[0]\n",
        "  log_likelihoods = []\n",
        "\n",
        "  for it in range(max_iter):\n",
        "      # E-step: responsibilities gamma_{ik}\n",
        "      gamma = np.zeros((N, K))\n",
        "      for k in range(K):\n",
        "          gamma[:, k] = pi_k[k] * gaussian_pdf(X, mu[k], Sigma[k])\n",
        "\n",
        "      # Normalize over k\n",
        "      gamma_sum = np.sum(gamma, axis=1, keepdims=True)\n",
        "      gamma = gamma / gamma_sum\n",
        "\n",
        "      # M-step\n",
        "      N_k = np.sum(gamma, axis=0)  # shape (K,)\n",
        "      pi_k = N_k / N\n",
        "\n",
        "      # Update means\n",
        "      mu_new = np.zeros_like(mu)\n",
        "      for k in range(K):\n",
        "          mu_new[k] = np.sum(gamma[:, k][:, None] * X, axis=0) / N_k[k]\n",
        "\n",
        "      # Enforce mean constraint: project onto respective helix\n",
        "      for k in range(K):\n",
        "          if k < 24:\n",
        "              mu_new[k] = project_to_helix(mu_new[k], which_helix=1)\n",
        "          else:\n",
        "              mu_new[k] = project_to_helix(mu_new[k], which_helix=2)\n",
        "\n",
        "      # Update covariances\n",
        "      Sigma_new = np.zeros_like(Sigma)\n",
        "      eps = 1e-3  # regularization\n",
        "      for k in range(K):\n",
        "          diff = X - mu_new[k]\n",
        "          weighted = gamma[:, k][:, None] * diff\n",
        "          Sigma_new[k] = (weighted.T @ diff) / N_k[k] + eps * np.eye(D)\n",
        "\n",
        "      # Compute log-likelihood\n",
        "      ll = 0.0\n",
        "      for i in range(N):\n",
        "          s = 0.0\n",
        "          for k in range(K):\n",
        "              # To ensure X[i] is a 1D vector here\n",
        "              s += pi_k[k] * gaussian_pdf(X[i], mu_new[k], Sigma_new[k])\n",
        "          ll += np.log(s + 1e-12)\n",
        "      log_likelihoods.append(ll)\n",
        "\n",
        "      # Check convergence\n",
        "      if it > 0 and abs(log_likelihoods[-1] - log_likelihoods[-2]) < tol:\n",
        "          break\n",
        "\n",
        "      mu, Sigma = mu_new, Sigma_new\n",
        "\n",
        "  return mu, Sigma, pi_k, np.array(log_likelihoods)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "UdCu5rdUYDrI"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "mu_em, Sigma_em, pi_em, ll_hist = run_em(X, mu, Sigma, pi_k)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "xa88ZutaY_0u"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
